<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 04-16-05 - New Kit for 5000i and 9000i Models to Seal Cold Air Door Leaks</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi041605" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>04-16-05</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>August, 2004</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>New Kit for 5000i and 9000i Models to Seal Cold Air Door Leaks</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="no" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>5500i</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>5600i</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>5900i</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9200i</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400i</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9900i</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A kit has been released to service 5000i and 9000i Models that have complaints of cold air door
                    leakage. The kit consists of pre-cut, adhesive backed sealing material and a plug to service both
                    the driver and passenger doors.
                </para>
                <para>The assembly plants have implemented the changes, to the driver side only, according to Table 1:
                </para>
                <table id="t0416051">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colname="col1" align="center" colwidth="1.11*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" align="center" colwidth="0.89*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Assembly Plant</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Start Date</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Chatham</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>03/08/04</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Escobedo</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>03/11/04</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Garland</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>03/19/04</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Refer to TSI-02-16-03 for an additional procedure to seal door air leaks.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t0416052">
                <tgroup cols="3" align="center">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.68*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.92*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col4" colwidth="0.40*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Kit Part Number</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2587778C91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Kit Contains the Following:</para>
                                <para>Item A</para>
                                <para>80 Inches Vinyl Tape (2)</para>
                                <para>Item B</para>
                                <para>7.5 X 4.5 Inch Pre-Cut 3M Tape Sheet (4)</para>
                                <para>Item C</para>
                                <para>10.25 X 17.2 Inches Pre-Cut 3M Tape Sheet (1)</para>
                                <para>Item D</para>
                                <para>Foam Plug (1)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2587470C1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Door Wedge Seal</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="6">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Following the instructions in Service Section S16021, remove the driver side interior
                    door trim and the inner door panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Clean inner door panel surfaces before applying the adhesive backed sealing material.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the street side of the inner door panel (Figure 1), apply Item A on the door panel
                    flange surface along the perimeter of the inner door panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the interior side of the inner door panel (Figure 2), apply Item B and Item C pre-cut
                    tape sheets to the areas indicated in Figure 2.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the foam plug, Item D, into the hole on the street side of the trim panel as
                    shown in Figure 3. This hole in the trim panel has the courtesy light harness running through it.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416051" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Street Side of Inner Door Panel (Driver Side)</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0416052" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Interior Side of Inner Door Panel</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0416053" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Street Side of Trim Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Courtesy Light Harness and Connector</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat for passenger side using Kit Items A and B only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Take a door wedge seal, Part Number 2587470C1, and install a Xmas tree fastener into the
                    hole at the narrow end of the seal (Figure 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416054" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416054.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Door Wedge Seal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Door Wedge Seal Without Xmas Tree Fastener</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Door Wedge Seal With Xmas Tree Fastener Shown Protruding From The Bottom Of The Wedge
                        Seal
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the door in the full open position locate the tubular weather seal along the "A"
                    pillar. Grasp the floor end of the tubular weather seal and twist the weather seal to expose the
                    opening on the back side of the seal and install the wedge seal into the tubular weather seal
                    (Figure 5).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416055" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416055.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Install Door Wedge Seal into Tubular Weather Seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the door wedge seal Xmas tree fastener into the door frame.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416056" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416056.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Completed Door Wedge Seal Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
